Tippy Walker https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tippy_Walker 0 Tippy Walker (born February 19, 1947) is a former American child actress, best known for her role in the film The World of Henry Orient (1964). Born Elizabeth Tipton Walker in New York City, her father was an engineer with Allied Chemical Corporation. She attended The Masters School in Dobbs Ferry, New York.After appearing in several television shows, such as Doctor Kildare and Peyton Place, and the female lead role in the film Jennifer on My Mind (which featured a young Robert De Niro), she retired from acting and opened an art gallery called "Out Of The Blue", near the Yale University campus. In 1984 she moved to New Haven, Connecticut. Tippy_Walker ( born February_19_,_1947 ) is a_former_American_child_actress , best_known for her_role in the_film The_World of Henry_Orient ( 1964 ) .
